Task: Replacing atomic-polyfill::AtomicUsize::fetch_add with critical-section on thumbv6m-none-eabi

 <p>Platform: rp2040 (2 Cortex-M0+ cores, thumbv6m-none-eabi)</p>
<p>Main branch of a project removed atomic-polyfill crate due to it being unmaintained. The code I'm rebasing used it for fetch_add. I have to replace following code:</p>
<pre><code>// self.channel_index is a atomic-polyfill::AtomicUsize
let index = self.channel_index.fetch_add(1, Ordering::Relaxed);
</code></pre>
<p>I can only use what thumbv6m-none-eabi and critical_section crate provide.</p>
<p>I've replaced it with:</p>
<pre><code>// self.channel_index is a core::sync::atomic::AtomicUsize
let index = critical_section::with(|_| {
    let old_val = self.channel_index.load(Ordering::Relaxed);
    self.channel_index.store(old_val + 1, Ordering::Relaxed);
    old_val
});
</code></pre>
<p>I feel that Ordering I've used is not correct. What is the correct Ordering and why?</p>


