  "main.rs": "//! Example: Hosting a child REPL process with asynchronous output handling
//! using rustyline and Unix signals. Child output appears immediately without
//! blocking the prompt.
//!
//! Note: Unix-only solution (relies on SIGUSR1). Requires bash for demo child process.
//!
//! How it works:
//! 1. Child process (bash) runs in background thread, outputs to channel
//! 2. On new output, thread sends SIGUSR1 to main process
